The genus
Exetastes GRAVENHORST
is a large genus of the Ichneumonidae , subfamily Banchinae with almost 170 species worldwide (
). Members of this genus are rather large (usually> 8 mm ) and have been found to attack mainly Lepidoptera of the family Noctuidae as hosts, at least in the West Palaearctic region (
). The genus is usually easy to identify, but the differentiation of the species is sometimes elusive.

